7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
8 Section 1. K.S.A. 46-1210 is hereby amended to read as follows: 46-
9 1210. (a) There is hereby established the legislative research department
10 whose head shall be the director of legislative research and who shall be
11 appointed by the legislative coordinating council to serve under its the
12 direction of the council. The director of legislative research may be
13 removed from office by a vote of five (5) members of the legislative
14 coordinating council taken at any regular meeting of such council. The
15 director of legislative research shall receive such compensation as is
16 determined by the legislative coordinating council. Such director, and any
17 of his or her such director's assistants specified by the legislative
18 coordinating council, shall receive expenses and allowances for in-state
19 and out-of-state travel as is provided by law for members of the
20 legislature. Such director shall appoint such assistants and employees of
21 the legislative research department as are authorized by the legislative
22 coordinating council and shall set their compensation subject to the
23 approval of such council. Such director and all assistants and employees of
24 the legislative research department shall be in the unclassified service.
25 (b) The legislative research department shall perform legislative
26 research functions and such other duties as are directed by the legislative
27 coordinating council.
28 (c) The legislative research department shall provide staff services to
29 all meetings of special committees, select committees, joint committees
30 and standing committees meeting when the legislature is not in session,
31 and to the extent possible, accomplish the following:
32 (1) Assist each committee chairman chairperson in planning the work
33 of the committee, and in accordance with the chairman's chairperson's
34 instructions prepare an agenda for each meeting.
35 (2) Appropriately notify committee members, staff and other

