1 interested persons of meeting times and other information as directed by
2 the committee chairman chairperson.
3 (3) Prepare minutes of each committee meeting to show attendance,
4 disposition of agenda items, tentative and final committee decisions and
5 staff instructions, and such other matters as may be helpful to the work of
6 the committee.
7 (4) Prepare and present research information in accordance with
8 committee instructions or instructions of the committee chairman
9 chairperson.
10 (5) Obtain attendance of persons for committee presentations or
11 testimony. In cases of compulsory process, work with the office of revisor
12 of statutes and office of attorney general to obtain satisfactory results.
13 (6) Prepare interim reports of committee work when the same is such
14 reports are requested of a committee by the legislative coordinating
15 council. Any such report shall have committee approval before
16 transmission.
17 (7) Prepare final a committee report in accordance with committee
18 instructions; the same to. Such report shall include relevant information,
19 committee policy recommendations, and to the extent possible, appropriate
20 bill drafts prepared by the office of revisor of statutes.
21 (8) Receive and analyze agency requests for appropriations and
22 prepare fiscal information for appropriate legislative committees.
23 (d) Special committees, select committees and standing committees
24 are expected to shall utilize the foregoing such staff services to the extent
25 the same are as available in making all studies.
26 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 46-1212a is hereby amended to read as follows: 46-
27 1212a. (a) There is hereby established the division of legislative
28 administrative services whose head shall be the director of legislative
29 administrative services and who shall be appointed by the legislative
30 coordinating council to serve under its the direction of the council. The
31 director of legislative administrative services may be removed from office
32 by a vote of five (5) members of the legislative coordinating council taken
33 at any regular meeting of such council. The director of legislative
34 administrative services shall receive such compensation as is determined
35 by the legislative coordinating council. Such director, and any of such
36 director's assistants specified by the legislative coordinating council, shall
37 receive expenses and allowances for in-state and out-of-state travel as is
38 provided by law for members of the legislature. Such director shall appoint
39 such assistants and employees of the division of legislative administrative
40 services as are authorized by the legislative coordinating council and shall
41 set their compensation subject to the approval of such council. Such
42 director and all assistants and employees of the division of legislative
43 administrative services shall be in the unclassified service.

